docs(api-ref): rounded box + zebra striping for the schema table

1. Rounded border on all four corners of the Schema table, matching the Example
   tab's .json-block. Done WITHOUT overflow:hidden on .schema-panel (that would clip
   the right-most header icon's tooltip at the panel edge — the Example tab is immune
   only because its right-most control is the tooltip-less Copy button): instead the
   header rounds the top corners and .schema-table-scroll clips its own bottom
   corners (a sibling of the header, so the tooltip is never clipped).

2. True zebra striping — odd rows emphasis-100 (darker), even rows the background,
   alternating every rendered row (nth-child, so it stays correct across
   expand/collapse), replacing the old parent-vs-leaf shading. Header row bumped to
   emphasis-200 to stay distinct from the odd stripe; parent rows keep their bold
   field name for tree structure; the example code-chip bumped to emphasis-200 so it
   stays visible on odd rows.

3. The Expand-all/Collapse-all tooltip now behaves consistently with the Example tab
   — resolved by (1) keeping the panel/header overflow visible, so the tooltip
   renders in full exactly as in the Example tab.

Also: inset the scroll-region focus ring (outline-offset) so it isn't clipped by the
table-scroll's new overflow:hidden, and drop the now-redundant 1px ring from the
full-bleed box-shadow (the panel has a real border now).
